videos.description: Alabama's Riley Norris does his best Odell Beckham Jr. impersonation by leaping high into the air to make the one-handed steal, and keeping his feet in-bounds before calling timeout to keep possession.
videos.headline: How to look like Odell Beckham on the basketball court

videos.description: 1H (4:49) ALA Brandon Austin made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Retin Obasohan.
videos.headline: B. Austin made Three Point Jumper to give Alabama its first lead of the game.

videos.description: Texas A&M leaves Riley Norris open from way behind the 3-point line, so the Alabama guard lets it fly and hits.
videos.headline: If you're open, shoot the ball, no matter how far away you are
D. Hall has 3 chances to make an easy layup, misses all of them before being fouled.

videos.description: 2H (16:52) TAMU Jalen Jones made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Anthony Collins.  ALA Arthur Edwards made Three Point Jumper. Assisted by Justin Coleman.
videos.headline: J. Jones made Three Point Jumper, Alabama's Arthur Edwards responds with his own.

videos.description: Alabama native and American Idol season 5 winner Taylor Hicks in attendance.
videos.headline: Alabama native and American Idol season 5 winner Taylor Hicks in attendance.

videos.description: Texas A&M's Jalen Jones cuts into the lane goes way above the rim to throw down the nasty, two-handed slam on Alabama.
videos.headline: Look out below! Jones is dunking from way up high
R. Obasohan makes tough layup in transition, then TAMU Admon Gilder goes down the other way for a layup while fouled.

videos.description: Alabama coach Avery Johnson explains how he's been able to get his team to overachieve this season following its victory over Texas A&M.
videos.headline: Alabama picks up fourth win over a ranked team this season
